cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO

The paper deals with image synthesis using machine learning algorithms, specifically convolutional neural networks (CNNs). This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. The paper also involves training on a large dataset, which is a common theme in machine learning research, placing it in the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves predicting occluded rays and improving depth estimation, which are tasks commonly associated with artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories.
